To prepare this dessert, start by freezing ripe bananas until they are solid. Then, blend the frozen bananas in a food processor until they are creamy and smooth. Add cocoa powder and a splash of almond milk to the banana mixture and blend until well combined. Serve the banana ice cream in bowls and sprinkle with chopped almonds for a crunchy texture and nutty flavor. This dessert is dairy-free, gluten-free, and naturally sweetened with the bananas, making it a great option for anyone with dietary restrictions or looking to reduce their sugar intake.
